node.text:
Some digital watercolor pieces I’ve done! 🌼 Made with @maxulichney’s watercolor brush set ✨ Before I started drawing digitally, my favorite medium was watercolor! Nowadays I prefer digital art over traditional, but it’s fun to explore a traditional aesthetic digitally ☺️ What’s your favorite traditional medium? ✨ 
 
I make tutorials & drawing videos on my Patreon! 💌 Once you join you’ll get access to over 50+ tutorial videos & step-by-steps, real-time process videos, cozy draw with me videos, my custom brush set, studio vlogs, & more ✨ the link is in my bio! ☁️

node.text:
River study 🏞✨ Swipe to see my reference! I’m trying to practice drawing environments with a person in them, which is something I tend to avoid 🙈 but I want to get better at it so here we go! ☺️ I filmed the full drawing process for a real-time process video and it’s posted on my Patreon! 💌 Patrons get to see each step of the drawing process at a slower pace, see my full screen while I draw, how I work with brushes & layers, and more 🌻 The link is in my bio! What are you guys currently trying to improve in your work? ✨

The link is in my bio if you wanna check it out 🌲🪵

node.text:
Sketching some fox studies 🦊✨ I love taking little breaks from drawing characters to study other subject matter occasionally, just to refresh my creativity 😌 and I find animals so relaxing to draw! 🌼 This week I’m working on a step-by-step tutorial for Patreon about how to draw foxes so this is fun practice! 🥰 What do you do to refresh your creativity? ✨

I make tutorials & drawing videos on my Patreon! 💌 Once you join you’ll get access to over 50+ tutorial videos & step-by-steps, real-time process videos, cozy draw with me videos, my custom brush set, studio vlogs, & more ✨ the link is in my bio! ☁️
